        " magazine November 1961 Pages 112–115 et al     The United States ended federal funding for the shelters in the 1970s.  In 2017, New York City began removing the yellow signs since members of the public are unlikely to find viable food and medicine inside those rooms.        Similar projects have been undertaken in ": null
